Tag.name: automatedDownload
Tag.Property: True means fully automatic, False means display recipe screen

EventScripts.Event:
#----------------------- def longProcess(tagPath = tagPath, val = currentValue.value): from ils.recipeToolkit.download import automatedDownloadHandler automatedDownloadHandler(tagPath, val) #-----------------------
# I'm not sure if it is a characteristic of my development system, or of OPC, or # of my Kepware OPC server, but whenever I restart my gateway this trigger fires as # if the OPC tag received a new value. Since it is highly unlikely for an # automated download to be requested at the same time as the gateway restarts this will # check to see that the system has been running for at least 30 seconds before # honoring any automated download requests. runningSeconds = system.tag.read("[~]Recipe/Constants/runningSeconds").value if runningSeconds != None and currentValue.value != "" and runningSeconds > 30: system.util.invokeAsynchronous(longProcess)

Tag.name: insertSQL
Tag.Property: After creating an instance manuall give this tag a value with the insert SQL. For example to update a property of a quant output. update DtQuantOutput set setpointHighLimit = ? where QuantOutputName = 'VCC205_Target'. The ? is a placeholder for value that is updated to setpointHighLimit and is used in the system funtion system.db.runPrepUpdate. Refer to Ignition manual for details.

Tag.name: triggerTag
Tag.Property:
This tag shows value in database. If database value updated ten value tag automatically update.
value <-> triggerTag
triggerTag is the database field. value tag just a tag you can change in Ignition.
After creating an instance override the SQL Query propery of this tag with the specific query. For example, if a specific property of a quant output is required the serial may be "select setpointHighLimit from DtQuantOutputs where QuantOutputName = 'VCC205_TARGET'.
This tag has a tag change script that will update the value tag when this value changes from the database.

EventScripts.Event:
# Read qualified value for value tag val = system.tag.read("[.]value").value
# Check if value and trigger value the same if not update value if val != currentValue.value: # currentValue is trigger tag system.tag.write("[.]value", currentValue.value)

EventScripts.Event:
""" This tag event script manages by the running state of WinApp CRx_HB & invokes the crx-recipe - if cr-x grade and cat-is-in then turn apps & structure data collection on - if cr-x grade and cat is out then turn off apps only - if not(c-rx grade) then turn apps & structure data collection off """
""" This import for reading values from chart """ import system.ils.blt.diagram as script """ Write datum import """ from ils.io.api import writeDatum
""" Get current grade for recipe enforcement """ grade = system.tag.read("[.]../../RLA3/Grade/grade").value
""" Check if c-rx is running and cat-in """ cRxGradeRunning = getBlockState("CrxProductQuality/PlantStatus/PlantStatus", "CRxGRadeRunning") catAndC2IsIn = getBlockState("CstrProductQuality/CstrPlantStatus/CstrPlantStatusSchematics", "CatAndC2IsIn")
if cRxGradeRunning == ".true" and catAndC2IsIn == ".true": status, errorMessage = writeDatum("Site/CRX/Status OPC/CRX_HB_STATE", 1) """ The original code would activate items below crx-data-activatable-subwksp onjects. These were either OPC items or trends. We could make the opc objects in a driven scanclass is required and forcibly enable/disable charts. Let's see how it works then decide if required. """
